<br>
The 24 hours becomes pro rated too, 12 hours online + 3 1/2 days offline = max time allowed.<br>
<br>
Many, many people die and think, 'to hell with it, I've had enough tonight, I'll get it later, ... let me see... which twink shall I play ?'<br>
<br>
Many younger players share accounts with family members, and when they log of their character, the other logs on.<br>
Same account, same time online.<br>
<br>
Guides and GM's do not enjoy telling people that they have nothing left, its one of the worst things you have to tell someone. Policys are strict, but the GM does have a little leeway. Remember that over every GM (server GM), is a Lead GM (A few servers) and so on.<br>
<br>
They are all accountable to someone further on up the line.<br>
<br>
Follow it thru, e mail again, but be really sure that no one was on your account, in fact, ask them to tell you which character was logged in and where.<br>
Our GM's are pretty good, persevere, its not instant, a character restore is a lot of work, and takes time.<br>
